HEADWORD: Metemptosis
<hw>Met`emp*to"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<?/ beyond, after + <?/ a falling upon, fr. <?/ to fall in or upon; <?/
in + <?/ to fall.]</ety> <fld>(Chron.)</fld> <def>The suppression of a
day in the calendar to prevent the date of the new moon being set a day
too late, or the suppression of the bissextile day once in 134 years.
The opposite to this is the <xex>proemptosis</xex>, or the addition of a
day every 330 years, and another every 2,400 years.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metencephalon</ent>⟦br⟧
